def chemo_side_effects(percent_hair_loss):
    if percent_hair_loss <= 20:
        return ["Nausea", "Fatigue", "Loss of appetite"] 
    elif percent_hair_loss <= 40:
         return ["Nausea", "Fatigue", "Loss of appetite", "Mouth sores"]
    elif percent_hair_loss <= 60:
         return ["Nausea", "Fatigue", "Loss of appetite", "Mouth sores", "Anemia"]      
    elif percent_hair_loss <= 80:
         return ["Nausea", "Fatigue", "Loss of appetite", "Mouth sores", "Anemia", "Infection"]        
    else: 
         return ["Nausea", "Fatigue", "Loss of appetite", "Mouth sores", "Anemia", "Infection", "Neuropathy"]
```

The function uses if/elif conditional logic to check which percentage range the hair loss falls in, and returns the corresponding list of three side effects.

